@0    = ~<CHARNAME>, we are together again, at last! I have yearned for this so eagerly these past months, and finally, finally, it's come true. You are here, by my side.~ [c#ablank]
@1    = ~...I lack the words to properly describe the joy I am feeling. I am so happy you are here.~
@2    = ~I am happy to have you back, too, Ajantis!~
@3    = ~Yes, it's good we are together again.~
@4    = ~Ajantis, your desire to be with me couldn't have been too great, considering you preferred to march through the mountains instead of search for me.~
@5    = ~Yes, but let us move on and talk at another time, Ajantis.~
@6    = ~Ajantis... I am no longer your beloved.~
@7    = ~You wrong me with these words, beloved. I hope I can convince you otherwise.~
@8    = ~I am relieved to hear that.~
@9    = ~You... do you mean this seriously?~
@10   = ~Yes, let us end the engagement.~
@11   = ~No, what am I saying? Everything is all right, Ajantis, my betrothed.~
@12   = ~Are... are you still my beloved?~
@13   = ~Yes, Ajantis, my betrothed.~
@14   = ~No, I am not. I want us to end the engagement.~
@15   = ~Let us continue together, side by side, and search for your enemy.~
@16   = ~It-it is nice to see you united. How terrible the time of your separation must have been!~
@17   = ~Not all of our... friends were as fortunate as we. Maybe you should not feel too troubled you were not there with <CHARNAME>, Ajantis.~
@18   = ~Minsc and Boo greet their old friend! It is nice to see that nothing happened to him, is it not, Boo?~
@19   = ~Minsc greets his old friend! Minsc is desperate, because Boo was stolen from him. Now my old friend will help me find him, yes?~
@20   = ~Humph, stop fussing, will ya?~
@21   = ~Yes, yes, it is very nice to see you again, etcetera, etcetera (this ape goes too far with his courtly behavior.)~
@22   = ~What a wonderful reunion. I hear bells ring and soft voices sing. Let us join this joyous melody!~
@23   = ~Greetings, Sir Ajantis. I hope you will use your prolonged life span and do good, as you have sworn.~
@24   = ~Yes, your joy is written on your face.~
@25   = ~Now he is back, your long-lost knight. I hope he can control himself, if only around me.~
@26   = ~It is always a good thing to meet friends again.~
@27   = ~Greetings, Sir knight. I am looking forward to uniting our forces.~
@28   = ~You surely seem to be happy, but you haven't found your balance in nature yet.~
@29   = ~Oh, yes, this reunion reminds me of the one with aunt Berti... Is anyone listening?~
@30   = ~How nice to see you again, Ajantis. <CHARNAME> missed you, that is for sure.~
@31   = ~What a joy to see you back unharmed, comrade.~
@32   = ~Here you are, shining brightly in you knightly honors. Disgusting.~
@33   = ~Ah, it warms my old soul to see you two so happy.~ 
@34   = ~But enough interruption. We shall be silent and step aside, so as not to disturb the two lovers.~
@35   = ~But enough interruption. I shall be silent and step aside, so as not to disturb the two lovers.~
@36   = ~I can hardly believe my luck. I will stay close to you, <CHARNAME>, and support you with the best of my abilities.~
@37   = ~By Helm! That is grim news, beloved!~ [c#ajan19]
@38   = ~The powerful mage, Irenicus, took you captive and tortured you?! What a gruesome deed! Just... just the thought makes me tremble with helpless anger!~
@39   = ~And now our friend Imoen, who has also suffered horrible torments, was abducted by the Cowled Wizards along with him?~
@40   = ~Yes, that is how it went. I need you to win this fight, Ajantis.~
@41   = ~Well, now you know what will await you.~
@42   = ~Do we have to talk about it? I don't like being reminded of it.~
@43   = ~You have my full support, <CHARNAME>.~
@44   = ~That I understand very well. I wish I could have helped you.~
@45   = ~The thought of what happened to you is nearly unbearable. I... I... (inhales) I will not rest until this villain is found and your tortures are avenged!~
@46   = ~And now our friend Imoen, who has also suffered horrible torments, was abducted by the Cowled Wizards along with him... and you were approached for help by the Shadow Thieves?!~
@47   = ~Yes, that is how it is. I need you to win this fight, Ajantis.~
@48   = ~Do we have to talk about it? I don't like being reminded of what happened.~
@49   = ~And that is not all! He stole your soul, without which you will lose yourself to your dark side. The thought makes me furious!~
@50   = ~Now I have a great desire to tell you what has happened to me since our separation.~
